Adjust oven rack to center position and preheat oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Whisk peanut sauce and peanut butter in a medium bowl until smooth. Spread sauce over the pizza crust. Spread chicken then the red pepper over pizza; bake until hot and crisp, 12 to 14 minutes. Remove pizza and sprinkle with carrots, green onion and cilantro. Cut into pieces and serve.